#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.243"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.243:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.243:0.2"
msgid "19. Āsīvisavagga"
msgstr "19. The Simile of the Vipers"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 243. Avassutapariyāyasutta → avassuto (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.243:0.3"
msgid "243. Avassutapariyāyasutta"
msgstr "243. The Explanation on the Corrupt"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.183"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near "
"Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

#. VAR: santhāgāraṃ → saṇṭhāgāraṃ (s1-3) | sandhāgāraṃ (mr)
#. VAR: anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ → anajjhāvutthaṃ (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.243:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ navaṃ santhāgāraṃ "
"acirakāritaṃ hoti anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā "
"manussabhūtena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a new town hall had recently been constructed for the "
"Sakyans of Kapilavatthu. It had not yet been occupied by an ascetic or "
"brahmin or any person at all."

msgctxt "sn35.243:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho "
"kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to "
"one side, and said to him:"

#. VAR: acirakāritaṃ → acirakāritaṃ hoti (bj, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.243:1.4"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ navaṃ santhāgāraṃ acirakāritaṃ "
"anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā manussabhūtena."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, a new town hall has recently been constructed for the Sakyans of "
"Kapilavatthu. It has not yet been occupied by an ascetic or brahmin or any "
"person at all."

msgctxt "sn35.243:1.5"
msgid "Taṃ, bhante, bhagavā paṭhamaṃ paribhuñjatu."
msgstr "May the Buddha be the first to use it,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:1.6"
msgid ""
"Bhagavatā paṭhamaṃ paribhuttaṃ pacchā kāpilavatthavā sakyā paribhuñjissanti."
msgstr "and only then will the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu use it."

msgctxt "sn35.243:1.7"
msgid "Tadassa kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That would be for the lasting welfare and happiness of the Sakyans of "
"Kapilavatthu.”"

msgctxt "sn35.243:1.8"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.184"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: sabbasanthariṃ → sabbasantharisanthataṃ (s1-3) | sabbasanthariṃ santhataṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.243:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena navaṃ santhāgāraṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā sabbasanthariṃ santhāgāraṃ santharitvā "
"āsanāni paññāpetvā udakamaṇikaṃ patiṭṭhāpetvā telappadīpaṃ āropetvā yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, the Sakyans got up from their "
"seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. "
"Then they went to the new town hall, where they spread carpets all over, "
"prepared seats, set up a water jar, and placed a lamp. Then they went back "
"to the Buddha and told him of their preparations, saying:"

#. VAR: sabbasantharisanthataṃ → sabbasanthariṃ santhataṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.243:2.2"
msgid ""
"“sabbasantharisanthataṃ, bhante, santhāgāraṃ, āsanāni paññattāni, "
"udakamaṇiko patiṭṭhāpito, telappadīpo āropito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.3"
msgid "Yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, sir, come at your convenience.”"

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena yena "
"navaṃ santhāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ "
"pavisitvā majjhimaṃ thambhaṃ nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the new town "
"hall together with the Saṅgha of mendicants. Having washed his feet he "
"entered the town hall and sat against the central column facing east."

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.5"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhusaṃghopi kho pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ pavisitvā pacchimaṃ bhittiṃ "
"nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi bhagavantaṃyeva purakkhatvā."
msgstr ""
"The Saṅgha of mendicants also washed their feet, entered the town hall, and "
"sat against the west wall facing east, with the Buddha right in front of "
"them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.6"
msgid ""
"Kāpilavatthavā sakyā pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ pavisitvā puratthimaṃ "
"bhittiṃ nissāya pacchimābhimukhā nisīdiṃsu bhagavantaṃyeva purakkhatvā."
msgstr ""
"The Sakyans of Kapilavatthu also washed their feet, entered the town hall, "
"and sat against the east wall facing west, with the Buddha right in front of "
"them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā kāpilavatthave sakye bahudeva rattiṃ dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uyyojesi:"
msgstr ""
"The Buddha spent most of the night educating, encouraging, firing up, and "
"inspiring the Sakyans with a Dhamma talk. Then he dismissed them:"

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.8"
msgid "“abhikkantā kho, gotamā, ratti."
msgstr "“The night is getting late, Gotamas."

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.9"
msgid "Yassadāni kālaṃ maññathā”ti."
msgstr "Please go at your convenience.”"

msgctxt "sn35.243:2.10"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied the Sakyans. They got up from their seat, bowed, and "
"respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right, before leaving."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkantesu kāpilavatthavesu sakyesu āyasmantaṃ "
"mahāmoggallānaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"And then, soon after the Sakyans had left, the Buddha addressed Venerable "
"Mahāmoggallāna:"

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.2"
msgid "“vigatathinamiddho kho, moggallāna, bhikkhusaṃgho."
msgstr ""
"“Moggallāna, the Saṅgha of mendicants is rid of dullness and drowsiness."

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.3"
msgid "Paṭibhātu taṃ, moggallāna, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammī kathā."
msgstr "Give them some Dhamma talk as you feel inspired."

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.4"
msgid "Piṭṭhi me āgilāyati;"
msgstr "My back is sore,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.5"
msgid "tamahaṃ āyamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I’ll stretch it.”"

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Mahāmoggallāna replied."

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapetvā dakkhiṇena passena "
"sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi, pāde pādaṃ accādhāya, sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ "
"manasi karitvā."
msgstr ""
"And then the Buddha spread out his outer robe folded in four and lay down in "
"the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—"
"mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up."

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.8"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Venerable Mahāmoggallāna addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.9"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.10"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.11"
msgid "Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:"
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said this:"

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.12"
msgid "“avassutapariyāyañca vo, āvuso, desessāmi, anavassutapariyāyañca."
msgstr "“I will teach you the explanation of the corrupt and the uncorrupted."

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.13"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.14"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn35.243:3.15"
msgid "Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:"
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.185"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:4.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ, āvuso, avassuto hoti?"
msgstr "“And how is someone corrupt?"

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe adhimuccati, appiyarūpe "
"rūpe byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassatī viharati parittacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with the eye. If it’s pleasant they hold "
"on to it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness "
"of the body unestablished and their heart restricted. "

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.3"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te "
"uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom "
"where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left "
"over."

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.4"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "They hear a sound … smell an odor … taste a flavor … feel a touch …"

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.5"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme adhimuccati, appiyarūpe dhamme "
"byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassatī ca viharati parittacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"know a thought with the mind. If it’s pleasant they hold on to it, but if it’"
"s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body "
"unestablished and a limited heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.6"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te "
"uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom "
"where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left "
"over."

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, āvuso, bhikkhu avassuto cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu … pe …"
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who is corrupt when it comes to sights known by "
"the eye,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.8"
msgid "avassuto jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu … pe …"
msgstr "sounds … smells … tastes … touches …"

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.9"
msgid "avassuto manoviññeyyesu dhammesu."
msgstr "thoughts known by the mind."

#. VAR: labhateva → labhatheva (s2, s3) | labhetha (mr)
#. VAR: labhati → labhetha (s3, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.243:4.10"
msgid ""
"Evaṃvihāriñcāvuso, bhikkhuṃ cakkhuto cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati labhateva "
"māro otāraṃ, labhati māro ārammaṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant lives like this, if Māra approaches their eye he finds a "
"vulnerability and gets hold of them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.11"
msgid ""
"jivhāto cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati, labhateva māro otāraṃ, labhati māro "
"ārammaṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "If Māra approaches their ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.243:4.12"
msgid ""
"manato cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati, labhateva māro otāraṃ, labhati māro "
"ārammaṇaṃ."
msgstr "mind he finds a vulnerability and gets hold of them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.186"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, naḷāgāraṃ vā tiṇāgāraṃ vā sukkhaṃ kolāpaṃ terovassikaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a house made of reeds or straw that was dried up, "
"withered, and decrepit."

#. VAR: labhetheva → labhetha (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.243:5.2"
msgid ""
"Puratthimāya cepi naṃ disāya puriso ādittāya tiṇukkāya upasaṅkameyya, "
"labhetheva aggi otāraṃ, labhetha aggi ārammaṇaṃ;"
msgstr "If a person came with a burning grass torch from the east,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.3"
msgid ""
"pacchimāya cepi naṃ disāya puriso ādittāya tiṇukkāya upasaṅkameyya … pe …"
msgstr "west,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.4"
msgid "uttarāya cepi naṃ disāya … pe …"
msgstr "north,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.5"
msgid "dakkhiṇāya cepi naṃ disāya … pe …"
msgstr "south,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.6"
msgid "heṭṭhimato cepi naṃ … pe …"
msgstr "below,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.7"
msgid "uparimato cepi naṃ …"
msgstr "above,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.8"
msgid ""
"yato kutoci cepi naṃ puriso ādittāya tiṇukkāya upasaṅkameyya, labhetheva "
"aggi otāraṃ labhetha aggi ārammaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"or from anywhere, the fire would find a vulnerability, it would get a "
"foothold."

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.9"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, evaṃvihāriṃ bhikkhuṃ cakkhuto cepi naṃ māro "
"upasaṅkamati, labhateva māro otāraṃ, labhati māro ārammaṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a mendicant lives like this, if Māra approaches their "
"eye he finds a vulnerability and gets hold of them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.10"
msgid "jivhāto cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati … pe …"
msgstr "If Māra comes in through their ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.11"
msgid ""
"manato cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati, labhateva māro otāraṃ, labhati māro "
"ārammaṇaṃ."
msgstr "mind he finds a vulnerability and gets hold of them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.12"
msgid "Evaṃvihāriñcāvuso, bhikkhuṃ rūpā adhibhaṃsu, na bhikkhu rūpe adhibhosi;"
msgstr "When a mendicant lives like this, they’re mastered by sights,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.13"
msgid "saddā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu, na bhikkhu sadde adhibhosi;"
msgstr "sounds,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.14"
msgid "gandhā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu, na bhikkhu gandhe adhibhosi;"
msgstr "smells,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.15"
msgid "rasā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu, na bhikkhu rase adhibhosi;"
msgstr "tastes,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.16"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu, na bhikkhu phoṭṭhabbe adhibhosi;"
msgstr "touches,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.17"
msgid "dhammā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu, na bhikkhu dhamme adhibhosi."
msgstr "and thoughts, they don’t master these things."

#. VAR: anadhibhū → anadhibhūto (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.243:5.18"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, bhikkhu rūpādhibhūto, saddādhibhūto, gandhādhibhūto, "
"rasādhibhūto, phoṭṭhabbādhibhūto, dhammādhibhūto, adhibhūto, anadhibhū, "
"adhibhaṃsu naṃ pāpakā akusalā dhammā saṃkilesikā ponobhavikā sadarā "
"dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who has been mastered by sights, sounds, smells, "
"tastes, touches, and thoughts. They’re mastered, not a master. Bad, "
"unskillful qualities have mastered them, which are defiled, leading to "
"future lives, hurtful, and resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old "
"age, and death."

msgctxt "sn35.243:5.19"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, avassuto hoti."
msgstr "That’s how someone is corrupt."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:6.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, anavassuto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is someone uncorrupted?"

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe nādhimuccati, "
"appiyarūpe rūpe na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati "
"appamāṇacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with the eye. If it’s pleasant they don’t "
"hold on to it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with "
"mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.3"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te uppannā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where "
"those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over."

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.4"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "They hear a sound … smell an odor … taste a flavor … feel a touch …"

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.5"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme nādhimuccati, appiyarūpe dhamme na "
"byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati appamāṇacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"know a thought with the mind. If it’s pleasant they don’t hold on to it, and "
"if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the "
"body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.6"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te uppannā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where "
"those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over."

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, bhikkhu anavassuto cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu … pe …"
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who is uncorrupted when it comes to sights known "
"by the eye,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.8"
msgid "anavassuto manoviññeyyesu dhammesu."
msgstr "sounds … smells … tastes … touches … thoughts known by the mind."

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.9"
msgid ""
"Evaṃvihāriñcāvuso, bhikkhuṃ cakkhuto cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati, neva "
"labhati māro otāraṃ, na labhati māro ārammaṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant lives like this, if Māra approaches their eye he doesn’t "
"find a vulnerability or get hold of them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.10"
msgid "jivhāto cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati … pe …"
msgstr "If Māra approaches their ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.243:6.11"
msgid ""
"manato cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati, neva labhati māro otāraṃ, na labhati māro "
"ārammaṇaṃ."
msgstr "mind he doesn’t find a vulnerability or get hold of them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.187"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:7.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kūṭāgāraṃ vā sālā vā bahalamattikā addāvalepanā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a bungalow or hall made of thick clay with its plaster "
"still wet."

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.2"
msgid ""
"Puratthimāya cepi naṃ disāya puriso ādittāya tiṇukkāya upasaṅkameyya, neva "
"labhetha aggi otāraṃ, na labhetha aggi ārammaṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "If a person came with a burning grass torch from the east,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.3"
msgid "pacchimāya cepi naṃ …"
msgstr "west,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.4"
msgid "uttarāya cepi naṃ …"
msgstr "north,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.5"
msgid "dakkhiṇāya cepi naṃ …"
msgstr "south,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.6"
msgid "heṭṭhimato cepi naṃ …"
msgstr "below,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.7"
msgid "uparimato cepi naṃ …"
msgstr "above,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.8"
msgid ""
"yato kutoci cepi naṃ puriso ādittāya tiṇukkāya upasaṅkameyya, neva labhetha "
"aggi otāraṃ, na labhetha aggi ārammaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"or from anywhere, the fire wouldn’t find a vulnerability, it would get no "
"foothold."

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.9"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, evaṃvihāriṃ bhikkhuṃ cakkhuto cepi naṃ māro "
"upasaṅkamati, neva labhati māro otāraṃ, na labhati māro ārammaṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a mendicant lives like this, if Māra approaches their "
"eye he doesn’t find a vulnerability or get hold of them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.10"
msgid ""
"manato cepi naṃ māro upasaṅkamati, neva labhati māro otāraṃ, na labhati māro "
"ārammaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If Māra comes in through their ear … nose … tongue … body … mind he doesn’t "
"find a vulnerability or get hold of them."

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.11"
msgid "Evaṃvihārī cāvuso, bhikkhu rūpe adhibhosi, na rūpā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu;"
msgstr "When a mendicant lives like this, they master sights,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.12"
msgid "sadde bhikkhu adhibhosi, na saddā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu;"
msgstr "sounds,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.13"
msgid "gandhe bhikkhu adhibhosi, na gandhā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu;"
msgstr "smells,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.14"
msgid "rase bhikkhu adhibhosi, na rasā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu;"
msgstr "tastes,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.15"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbe bhikkhu adhibhosi, na phoṭṭhabbā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu;"
msgstr "touches,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.16"
msgid "dhamme bhikkhu adhibhosi, na dhammā bhikkhuṃ adhibhaṃsu."
msgstr "and thoughts, they’re not mastered by these things."

#. VAR: dhammādhibhū, adhibhū, anadhibhūto → anadhibhūto kehici kilesehi (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.243:7.17"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, bhikkhu rūpādhibhū, saddādhibhū, gandhādhibhū, rasādhibhū, "
"phoṭṭhabbādhibhū, dhammādhibhū, adhibhū, anadhibhūto, adhibhosi te pāpake "
"akusale dhamme saṃkilesike ponobhavike sadare dukkhavipāke āyatiṃ "
"jātijarāmaraṇiye."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who has mastered sights, sounds, smells, tastes, "
"touches, and thoughts. They’re a master, not mastered. Bad, unskillful "
"qualities have been mastered by them, which are defiled, leading to future "
"lives, hurtful, and resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and "
"death."

msgctxt "sn35.243:7.18"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, anavassuto hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how someone is uncorrupted.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uṭṭhahitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha got up and said to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna:"

msgctxt "sn35.243:8.2"
msgid "“sādhu sādhu, moggallāna."
msgstr "“Good, good, Moggallāna!"

msgctxt "sn35.243:8.3"
msgid ""
"Sādhu kho tvaṃ, moggallāna, bhikkhūnaṃ avassutapariyāyañca "
"anavassutapariyāyañca abhāsī”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s good that you’ve taught this explanation of the corrupt and the "
"uncorrupted.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.188"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.243:9.1"
msgid "Idamavoca āyasmā mahāmoggallāno."
msgstr "This is what Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said,"

msgctxt "sn35.243:9.2"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "sn35.243:9.3"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what Mahāmoggallāna said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.243:9.4"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
